</h3><p class="sc-kHOZwM oQMan pf-52_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">The method of using an AED varies slightly depending on the patient:





















</p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-kYHfwS lkFAWj pf-54_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-xiLah hUMvDY pf-55_ pf-text-1"><strong>Adults and children over 8 years or weighing over 25kg</strong> - Apply the adult AED pads and follow the device's instructions.


































</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-xiLah hUMvDY pf-57_ pf-text-1"><strong>Children aged 1-8 years or under 25kg</strong> - Use paediatric pads if available. If not, adult pads may be used, ensuring they do not touch each other on the child's chest.


































